{
  "text": "The hemodynamic data are summarized in Table 1 . The baseline heart rates and blood pressures were lower than in pentobarbital-anesthetized rats (9) because of the cardiodepressant effects of ketamine-xylazine anesthesia [CITATION_1] . However, these baseline parameters were not different among the groups. Administration of the adenosine A 1 /A 2a receptor agonist AMP-579 produced a marked depression in heart rate and mean arterial pressure, with the former effect inhibited by the A 1 adenosine receptor antagonist DPCPX. The p38 MAPK inhibitor SB-203580 had no effect on heart rate or mean arterial pressure when given alone or before AMP-579 injection.",
